pulses.name: Gayfemboy: A Botnet Deliver Through a Four-Faith Industrial Router 0-day Exploit
pulses.description: Countless script kiddies, dreaming of getting rich, rush into the DDoS black-market industry armed with Mirai source code, imagining they can make a fortune with botnets. Reality, however, is harsh—these individuals arrive full of ambition but leave in dismay, leaving behind a series of Mirai variants that survive no more than 3–4 days. However, today’s focus, Gayfemboy, is an exception.

pulses.name: Gayfemboy botnet
pulses.description: Gayfemboy botnet, a unique and aggressive variant of Mirai that has been active since February 2024. It leverages 0-day exploit to target IoT devices and has over 15,000 daily active nodes(we registered the c2 domin)

pulses.name: Gayfemboy: A Botnet Deliver Through a Four-Faith Industrial Router 0-day Exploit.
pulses.description: A Mirai botnet variant has been found exploiting a newly disclosed security flaw impacting Four-Faith industrial routers since early November 2024 with the goal of conducting distributed denial-of-service (DDoS) attacks.
